# FARSITE Landscape File - Southern California Chaparral Test Case
# Format: X Y ELEVATION SLOPE ASPECT FUEL_MODEL
# Units: 
#   X, Y: meters
#   ELEVATION: meters above sea level
#   SLOPE: degrees (0-90)
#   ASPECT: degrees (0-360, where 0=North, 90=East, 180=South, 270=West)
#   FUEL_MODEL: NFFL fuel model number (4 = chaparral)
#
# This is a sample 100m x 100m domain representing typical Southern California
# chaparral terrain with moderate slopes facing southwest (typical fire-prone aspect).
# The terrain has variable slopes (10-35 degrees) consistent with coastal mountain
# foothills in Southern California where wildfires are common.
#
# Grid: 11x11 points spaced 10m apart (100m x 100m domain)

